-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group, Komercni Banka Are Active in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-17T14:41:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/czech-stocks-erste-group-komercni-banka-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
increased 0.7 percent to 907.8 by the end of trade in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   jumped 2 percent to 386.20
koruna, its biggest rally in more than two weeks. The Austrian
lender was rated buy in new coverage at VTB Capital.  Komercni Banka  AS (KOMB CP), a unit of Societe Generale SA,
added 1.8 percent to 3,415 koruna. Czech lenders have “ample
capital and liquidity” and stress tests show the country’s
financial system can withstand “substantial shocks,” the
 International Monetary Fund  said today in a report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
